THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 422A of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. The Division shall secure from appropriate law enforcement agencies
4 information on the background and personal history of a prospective employee or
5 prospective contractor, as applicable, of the Division.
6 2. A prospective employee or prospective contractor, as applicable, of the
7 Division must submit to the Division:
8 (a) Proof that he or she is a citizen of the United States or is lawfully entitled
9 to remain and work in the United States; and
10 (b) Two complete sets of fingerprints and written authorization to forward
11 those fingerprints to the Central Repository for submission to:
12 (1) The Federal Bureau of Investigation for a report on his or her
13 background; and
14 (2) Any appropriate law enforcement agency that the Division deems
15 necessary.
16 3. The Division shall submit the fingerprints submitted pursuant to
17 subsection 2 to the Central Repository for submission to:
18 (a) The Federal Bureau of Investigation for a report on the background of
19 the prospective employee or prospective contractor, as applicable; and
20 (b) Any appropriate law enforcement agency that the Division deems
21 necessary.
22 4. When a report from the Federal Bureau of Investigation or any
23 information from an appropriate law enforcement agency is received by the
24 Central Repository, the Central Repository shall immediately forward a copy of
25 the report or the information to the Division.
26 5. The Division shall conduct an investigation of each employee and
27 contractor of the Division pursuant to this section at least once every 5 years after
28 the initial investigation.
29 6. Only the Central Repository may:
30 (a) Receive fingerprints from the Division for submission to the Federal
31 Bureau of Investigation pursuant to this section;
32 (b) Submit the fingerprints to the Federal Bureau of Investigation; and
33 (c) Receive a report from the Federal Bureau of Investigation based on the
34 submission of the fingerprints.
35 7. As used in this section:

